author: Chris Zeuthen
title: Thursday’s prep soccer results
text:
Auburn Riverside 6, Auburn 0 
Auburn Riverside’s powerhouse offense proved to be too much for their Trojan counterparts, and the Ravens seized a solid 6-0 victory. Led by Izzy Creighton’s first half hat trick, Natalie Lake took control of the second 40 minutes, scoring two goals of her own, as well as an early assist in the 43rd minute.
Garfield 4, Franklin 0 
Garfield’s Cameron Dacey dominated the field, scoring 3 of her 8 shots on goal, and providing an assist to teammate Noelle Kim.
